    Last week my team launched a li‚Äôl project called [Matterday](https://matterday.netlify.com/). Turns out switching to Netlify saves development teams one day a week *per developer*. That‚Äôs a lot of time! And we hope folks can spend that time on things that matter to them.

    The narrative portion of the site encourages folks to imagine what they could do with that time ‚Äî whether it be small changes to daily routines or taking big swings. As you know, a narrative-heavy website is just begging for some fun scrolling effects. And since I‚Äôm me, I wanted to see what I could do with just CSS.

    I started with a concept I used for [a previous version of andyet.com](https://web.archive.org/web/20200423144745/https://andyet.com/) that utilized fixed positioning and z-index to create layered scrolling artwork.

