    ## But why use CSS instead of JavaScript?

    Why do it like this? I love trying new things with CSS. It‚Äôs powerful and there are so many cool techniques to experiment with. For most animated scroll experiences, [Green Sock](https://greensock.com/) really is king and we recently used the heck out of it for the [Netlify homepage](https://www.netlify.com/) (shoutout to [Justin](https://justinchuan.com/), [Ryan](https://ryanmulligan.dev/), and [Sam](https://samtan.dev/) for amazing work there). So I figured, why not take a stab at something different? It‚Äôs just really fun.

